cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.CE, cs.PF, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the modeling and control of high-voltage direct-current transmission systems, which involves the use of electrical engineering concepts and techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems. The paper also involves the use of power flow equations and network topologies, which are related to the fields of electrical engineering and computer engineering. Hence, cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.CE (Computer Engineering) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the passivity properties of the system and proposes a PI control, which are related to the field of power electronics. Therefore, cs.PF (Power Electronics) is another likely category. Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance analysis, which are related to the field of distributed computing. Hence, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category.
